      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CAUSEWELUVADELAIDE (2) bounced back sharply here last time when making very light work of his rivals. Only rises slightly at the weights and looks a great chance to make it two on the bounce. MAXILDO (3) push forward and gave a great sight here when resuming, only to be grabbed on the line. Better for that hitout and draws the A1 again. Will prove tougher to reel in this time. MORLAIX (8) lost her rider last start here when sent out favourite over CAUSEWELUVADELAIDE. Prior form stacks right up, so have to give another chance. MAGIC PRINCESS (7) doesn't win out of turn but was much better last time at Bordertown when sticking on gamely into the placings. Gets a key switch in Pannell and draws well, so worth some thought. The stalwart FRANCE'S BOY (4) lines up at start 171 and will again push forward from his draw to give a sight. Can steal it if left alone, as seen so many times before.",
